Name: juvenile myelomonocytic leukemia
Definition: A myelodysplastic myeloproliferative neoplasm that is characterized by the uncontrolled growth of monocytes.

Name: atypical chronic myeloid leukemia
Definition: A myelodysplastic myeloproliferative neoplasm characterized by the principal involvement of the neutrophil series with leukocytosis and multilineage dysplasia. The neoplastic cells do not have a Philadelphia chromosome or the BCR/ABL fusion gene.
